			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A lot of the argument against FBoT being comparable to the level 65 spells seems to be that there is an innate superiority of being level 65 over being 61.  While certainly true, I've always thought of the 61-65 range as a very similar continuum.  Not like the difference between say, 1 and 5, or 20 and 25 even, when gaining a level meant something other than access to some new spells (noticeable mana/hp improvement, or for the 50's, much better aa's).  Sure there's some aa's you can't get until you're maxxed, but I've known a lot of people with characters far more powerful than myself who have stayed at level 62 to gain aa's better.
<br />

<br />
Anyway though, yeah I agree the bolts shouldn't shoot through walls.
<br />
Characters yes, other mobile objects maybe.
<br />

<br />
I never raid, but even in single group situations or solo, I've found they simply missed inexplicably a lot of the time and really didn't offer much bang for the hassle.  I stuck with evoc just because it's what I picked way back when.  As is now, I finally feel I have a good choice in specialization.  Given the rest of our spells are conjuration, I don't think conj. mages are slighted by this either.  Still plenty of advantages either way.
<br />

<br />
If you really want to make bolts truly bolt-like (or just return to how they were), let's maybe throw a bone in there, with some extra damage, or maybe double the chance for a crit?
<br />

<br />
In theory, rains are still the best bang for the buck though aren't they?  (at 3 waves plus 20% resists)
<br />

<br />
Just my ramblings for the moment,
<br />
Dretchulos
<br />
65th season mage, Torvonnilous</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
