			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The mana cost due to evocation spec and slow casting time are enough of a drawback IMO.  
<br />

<br />
There are also a few more drawbacks that haven't been talked about.
<br />

<br />
1.  FoT is a bolt vs instant damage.  This means the burst DPS is lower because it has to travel to the target after being cast.
<br />

<br />
2.  During that travel time, if you use any clickable item your bolt will not be focused.
<br />

<br />
3.  If the target dies while casting a bolt or during the travel time, you will still spend mana on it and the bolt will fly off into space.  If you were casting a standard DD you would not lose any mana.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=546815" target=_blank>Sarye Starfyre</a> 
<br />
Blood Cult
