<br />
Were you aware that you could start casting the next bolt before the first bolt even hit?
<br />

<br />
Bolts having delayed impact is in no way a drawback to the DPS the spell brings, becuase casting can start before the spell even lands on the mob.  Depending on you distance from the mob, you could even start casting your bolt earlier than I'd ever think of casting my nuke (on the pull?   and Yes, I've done it on mage and never got summoned the entire fight).  And whoever said agro was a drawback needs to get off that bandwagon.  I think we all have established the point that agro is in no way a drawback to any raiding mage.
<br />

<br />
If you cannot get your bolts to hit in a group you either suck really bad or are extremely lazy/slack.  Both of those are high possibilities in that case.
<br />

<br />
Bolts were designed to be very mana efficient with the drawbck of LoS and (back in the day) Elevation.  Bolts used to miss if someone was standing on a rock and was 4 feet higher up than you sometimes.
<br />

<br />
As for using bolts on a raid, there was never a problem as long as you could levitate yourself.  The hitbox of a PC is very small, and that's what blocks the bolt.  The graphics that you see on your screen means nothing.  That is why it was always easier to hit larger mobs on raids with bolts, they have a far larger hit box compared to smaller ones.  Think a drake in skyfire as opposed to Suled'Dar Shade, and yes I know it's Skyfire just using an example (I used WF on SDS anyways).
<br />

<br />
Bolts hitting through walls are not intended.  This isn't some thin tree model people.  This is the type of wall clerics hide behind to avoid AEs.  It's a bug plain and simple; and anyone who states otherwise I just really don't know what your mental condition is.  Changing bolts is no different than the fix to Reclaim Energy.  It was not intended and is causing imbalance in the game (other nukes get their mana drained, mages are AOK...  Just like Wizards having to med for 10 minutes while mages canni to full in 2).
<br />

<br />
A worse mana ratio would be ok?  I'd use Shock of Magic every Qvic raid if it went through walls and had a 300 Range, even if it hit for only 2k a blast.  No thanks.  Revert pls.
<br />

<br />
Have you bugged the clickie "bug"?  Or are you afraid that they will take a second look at bolts and change them back to their intended status?
<br />

<br />
I agree with Kirium on this issue.
<br />

<br />
