			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Bolts are the equivalent to artillery.  Artillery shells do not travel in straight lines.  Cruise missiles do not travel in straight lines.  Leave my photon torpedo just as it is.  Let the wizards and chanters with their 1khp skins/runes jump into the AE to nuke...they can take the hit.  Let us at least have some distinction with the longest range spell that we can arc around a wall.  I base this on the experience of having them chase people towards a hill, but never hit because the person got over the hill fast enough to cause the bolt to track right into the hill.  I've always fired my bolts out around a wall.  They don't "ignore" walls, but they can be aimed around them.  I tested a bit in Abysmal Sea...lots of buildings and obstacles.  I casted on a person...didnt check LOS to start casting, but the bolts never landed because they hit walls and the deck.  Aim up when I cast and it hit...arced up and right back down on my target.
<br />

<br />
"Bolts hitting through walls are not intended." - Again I'll say that they don't go through walls.  They go around them...or don't you remember the days when you could actually see them and control their path to arc over hills (I used to do this a LOT in PvP...sniping people by lobbing bolts over hills), around corners...ever watch them track a running player (probably not if you're on a blue server).
<br />

<br />
If you are facing a true obstacle and hitting a monster on the other side, then there's definitely something that needs looked at.  Only way you're going to prove that to me is with a movie.  I've yet to accomplish such a feat though.
<br />

<br />
The *only* thing I want changed about bolts is the graphic...I sure do miss watching them track people in PvP.
<br />

<br />
I sure don't get how SoE manages to give us a heavy hitting, versatile spell that is readily available (now this may or may not extend to the OOW version), and people are all up in arms about how unfair it is and how it makes our other nukes so worthless and how it should be looked at, torn apart, and nerfed into the ground.  If you think the nukes after FoT are so bad, try improving them instead of tearing down one of the good things we get.  Sounds an awful lot like the mages who complained how the bought PoP pets could outperform our epic...
<br />

<br />
Edit1:  Just tested some on a friend of mine while in Yxtta.  Would be nice if I could see them again, though.  Anyway, corner at Yxtta/Kod zoneline on the way to Uqua.  On the map the corner has a rock formation thats counted as wall (not an obstacle like some rocks/trees you can shoot through).  I was on wall near zoneline.  Target was around the corner next to the wall.  I fired along 4 points of the compass.  South, no hit, ran into wall.  East, no hit, apparently ran into wall.  North, hit, arced around corner and landed.  West, no hit, apparently hit the wall.  Rough test, but it proves my point.
<br />

<br />
I just want this out there before uninformed people saying "bolts ignore walls" like bolts are just going right through everything end up getting this nerfed.  Name another class that has a grenade-like weapon similar to this.<br />_________________<br />TJRii
<br />
Tuis Hajidodger &amp; Beefcake Zergbane
<br />
<Pandemonium>
<br />
Tallon Zek</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
