				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sounds like East Commons.  And I think I've had regular spells cast through there, but I'm not sure.  Expand your testing.  I'll take note of it next time I'm there...there's always someone to fight in EC (a regular highway between PoK and the Magus).
<br />

<br />
Use a hill.  South Ro has some good ones.  Put your face in the hill and try to cast on someone/something on the other side.  Then tilt your view up.  Then face 90 degree to one side, aim up.  Then try facing away from the hill.  I used to entertain myself often with 3rd person camera watching bolts back in the day...
<br />

<br />
I just dont want to see bolts nerfed because of what may be faulty geography.  The pillar next to the Magus camp in Butcher...95% sure you can bolt through it...a ranger was hitting me with arrows through it and I know you can cast nukes on people from the opposite side.  Its a nifty ambush point.
<br />

<br />
I don't mean to snap at you, I just don't want my favorite spell jacked just when it has finally reached perfection.<br />_________________<br />TJRii
<br />
Tuis Hajidodger &amp; Beefcake Zergbane
<br />
<Pandemonium>
<br />
Tallon Zek</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
